Minimum bond distance and bond tolerance

Even movement and fixed navbar bug

Mark long description as markdown

Rotation Enhancements (#7)

* Auto-Rotation at 30 fps via F1-3
* Center on Coordinates via C
* Rotate onto principal axes of rotation via T
* Readme update
* Version increment, now 0.2.x

Parse SMILES strings (#8)

Using RDKit as hard dependency
Config is now a traditional class

ASE and RDKit (#9)

RDKit and ASE are now optional dependencies

* Check beforehand which is installed and then handle input smartly.
* Whenever the called file does not exist, try to interpret als SMILES string or complain that neither ASE nor RDKit are available.

Character Buffer less silly (#11)

Character buffer was a cols x lines sized array containing strings, it is now a sparse list of tuples containing only the actual content. Should be a little more perfomant and a lot less silly.

Faster bond detection

Replaced the explicit python loop with a faster numpy equivalent

New Renderer Features

* Restructured most of the renderer code
* New Bond toggle (default): Fancy, dots, none
* New Fancy bond rendering that is angle based

Animation (#12)

* New Feature: .xyz Trajectories
* When opening an .xyz file with multiple frames, TAB cycles through them
* Known Issue: Principle Axes Transformation only applies to the currently displayed frame
* Side-effect: All files will be opened by the internal xyz reader first and only defer to other options if this fails

Animation fixes

* Fixed Off-center after frame change
* Added ability to go back one frame by pressing Shift+Tab
